<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">The species is named after its collection locality, Tsavo National Park in Kenya.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Kenya (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 37. Distribution map for Pampsilota leleupi, Pampsilota luederitzensis, Pampsilota nigeriae, Pampsilota tsavoensis, and Pampsilota zebra." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118807" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adults resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the mostly yellow colour of the abdomen and thorax underside, but differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the blackish dorsal part of mesepisternum, shape of the serrulae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 27–30" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 27 - 30. Pampsilota tsavoensis: 27. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 28. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 29. Lancet; 30. Serrulae 10 - 11." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures27-30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118800" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">29</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 27–30" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 27 - 30. Pampsilota tsavoensis: 27. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 28. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 29. Lancet; 30. Serrulae 10 - 11." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures27-30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118800" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">30</figureCitation>
), and in the morphology of the valvulae 3, which in 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are conspicuously divergent in dorsal view, with distinct denticles on the interior surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 27–30" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 27 - 30. Pampsilota tsavoensis: 27. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 28. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 29. Lancet; 30. Serrulae 10 - 11." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures27-30" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118800" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">28</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the valvulae 3 do not diverge distally, and are without denticles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 15–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 15 - 19. Pampsilota dahomeyanus: 15. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 16. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 17. Lancet; 18. Serrulae 10 - 11; 19. Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures15-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118793" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">16</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which only a single male is known, differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its predominantly yellow antenna and the bicoloured stigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
